The '''UCL Eastman Dental Institute''' is a [[dental school]] located in [[London]], [[United Kingdom]] and an academic department of the Faculty of Medical Sciences of [[University College London]] (UCL).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ucl.ac.uk/departments/academic-departments/|title=Academic Departments by Faculty|accessdate=17 September 2010|publisher=University College London}}</ref> It is based on [[Gray's Inn Road]] in the [[Bloomsbury]] district of [[Central London]] adjacent to the [[Eastman Dental Hospital]], with which it is closely associated.<ref name=introduction>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastman.ucl.ac.uk/about/directors_message/index.html|title=Introduction|accessdate=16 September 2010|publisher=UCL Eastman Dental Institute}}</ref><ref>{{citation |url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=_iE0JVcUDogC&pg=PA19 |title=The University of London, 1836-1986: an illustrated history |author=N. B. Harte}}</ref><ref>{{citation |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=YKlUuwX8xCEC&pg=PA83 |title=Walking London's medical history |author=Nick Black}}</ref>

The Institute is the largest postgraduate dental centre in [[Europe]], and together with the Eastman Dental Hospital forms one of the largest concentrations of oral health care specialists and research in Europe.<ref name=introduction/><ref name=bdj1>{{cite journal|author=|year=2007|title=The Eastman at 60 <U+2014> a history of the UCL Eastman Dental Institute|journal=British Dental Journal|volume=203|issue=|pages=551 - 554|doi=10.1038/bdj.2007.1040}}</ref> The Institute runs a [[Continuing professional development|CPD]] programme with the ''British Dental Journal'' which is one of the largest of its type, with around 14,000 dental care professionals enrolled.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastman.ucl.ac.uk/cpd/index.html|title=Welcome to Eastman CPD|accessdate=16 September 2010|publisher=UCL Eastman Dental Institute}}</ref>

==History==
[[File:Eastman Dental Hospital 1.jpg|150px|right|thumb|The [[Eastman Dental Hospital]].]]
In 1926 [[George Eastman]] donated <U+00A3>200,000 to fund the establishment of a dental clinic in London, after being approached by the Chairman of the [[Royal Free Hospital]], Lord Riddell, with donations of <U+00A3>50,000 each also made by Lord Riddell and the Royal Free honorary treasurer.<ref name=history>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastman.ucl.ac.uk/about/inside_instit/history_edi/index.html|title=A history of EDI|accessdate=16 September 2010|publisher=UCL Eastman Dental Institute}}</ref> On 20 November 1931, the Eastman Dental Clinic opened as part of the Royal Free Hospital. In 1948, the Eastman became independent of the Royal Free and became the postgraduate dental institute of the Postgraduate Medical Federation.<ref>{{citation |title=The Oxford companion to medicine |volume=1
 |year=1986 |quote=soon after the Second World War the Postgraduate Dental Institute was established in London at the Eastman Dental Hospital}}</ref> In 1949 the Eastman opened a department of pathology and microbiology and the first civilian [[oral hygiene]] school in the UK.<ref name=history/><ref name=bdj1/>

During the Directorship of Professor Frank Wilson (1950<U+2013>1959) a full department range was established at the Eastman, including children<U+2019>s, oral surgery, radiography and prosthetics.<ref name=history/><ref name=bdj1/> The Directorship of Sir Robert Bradlaw (1959<U+2013>1970) saw the Eastman<U+2019>s teaching concept altered, with MSc courses of the [[University of London]] being introduced.<ref name=history/> In 1988 the Eastman moved to the old Royal Free buildings on Gray's Inn Road and in 1992 the Eastman's name was changed to the Eastman Dental Institute (EDI).<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.qaa.ac.uk/reviews/reports/subjectlevel/q218_99.pdf |title=Eastman Dental Institute |publisher=[[Quality Assurance Agency for Higher Education]] |date=April 1999}}</ref> 

In October 1995 the Institute established a joint project with the Rutherford Appleton Laboratory to develop ultraviolet lasers to replace conventional dental drills.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/story.asp?storyCode=95367&sectioncode=26|title=Drill thrills to come|accessdate=26 April 2012|publisher=Times Higher Education|date=6 October 1995}}</ref> The Institute merged with University College London in 1999, becoming the UCL Eastman Dental Institute,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/education/2002/oct/22/highereducation.universitymergers|title=The merger and the man|accessdate=26 April 2012|publisher=The Guardian|date=22 October 2002}}</ref> and in 2002 it won the Queens Award for Higher Education.<ref name=history/><ref name=bdj1/>

==Research==
The Institute achieved top scores of 5 in both the 1996 and 2001 [[Research Assessment Exercise]]s and the Institute's research programme is one of only two oral themes to achieve national funding within an NHS Biomedical Research Centre, as part of the [[UCLH/UCL Comprehensive Biomedical Research Centre]].<ref name=eastmansixty>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastman.ucl.ac.uk/Eastman60BrochureFINAL.pdf|title=The Eastman Celebrating 60 years|accessdate=16 September 2010|publisher=UCL Eastman Dental Institute}}</ref> Both the Institute and the Eastman Dental Hospital are part of [[UCL Partners]], the largest academic health science centre in Europe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uclpartners.com/about-us|title=About us|accessdate=16 September 2010|publisher=UCL Partners}}</ref>

Research at the Institute is currently represented by three interdisciplinary divisions:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastman.ucl.ac.uk/research/index.html|title=Research at the UCL Eastman Dental Institute|accessdate=16 September 2010|publisher=UCL Eastman Dental Institute}}</ref>
*[http://www.eastman.ucl.ac.uk/research/BTE/index.html Biomaterials and Tissue Engineering Division]
*[http://www.eastman.ucl.ac.uk/research/CR/index.html Clinical Research Division]
*[http://www.eastman.ucl.ac.uk/research/MD/index.html Microbial Diseases Division]

==Education==
[[Image:UCL Portico Building.jpg|250px|right|thumb|The main portico of [[University College London]].]]
At postgraduate level the Institute currently offers the following masters programmes:<ref name=masters>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastman.ucl.ac.uk/eep/taught_programmes/masters_programmes/index.html|title=Masters Programmes|accessdate=16 September 2010|publisher=UCL Eastman Dental Institute}}</ref>

*MSc in Conservative Dentistry 
*MSc in Endodontics
*MSc in Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery
*MSc in Oral Medicine
*MSc in Restorative Dental Practice
*MSc in Special Needs Dentistry
*MClinDent in Endodontology
*MClinDent in Oral Surgery
*MClinDent in Orthodontics
*MClinDent in Periodontology
*MClinDent in Prosthodontics

The Institute offers a clinical doctorate programme in Paediatric Dentistry and an MSc in Dental Public Health through the UCL Department of Epidemiology and Public Health.<ref name=masters/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastman.ucl.ac.uk/eep/taught_programmes/ddent/index.html|title=Clinical Doctorate Programmes|accessdate=16 September 2010|publisher=UCL Eastman Dental Institute}}</ref>

The Institute also offers a large number of short courses, Certificate Programmes and Diploma Programmes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastman.ucl.ac.uk/eep/taught_programmes/index.html|title=Taught Programme Opportunities|accessdate=16 September 2010|publisher=UCL Eastman Dental Institute}}</ref>

==Library==
The Institute library contains around 3,000 books and 70 locally held journal titles, and also has access to many e-journals, e-books and online databases.<ref>{{cite book|title=Directory of special libraries and information centers, Volume 1, Part 5|first1=Cengage|last1=Gale|first2=Matthew|last2=Miskelly|publisher=Gale Research Co|year=2010|isbn=|page=2827|url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=vHxBAQAAIAAJ&q=Directory+of+special+libraries+and+information+centers+Volume+1,+Part+5&dq=Directory+of+special+libraries+and+information+centers+Volume+1,+Part+5&hl=en&sa=X&ei=cWKZT8vEOYGu0QWr-PzzBQ&ved=0CDMQ6AEwAA}}</ref><ref name=library>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastman.ucl.ac.uk/departments/others/library/ic_about/index.html|title=Eastman Library|accessdate=16 September 2010|publisher=UCL Eastman Dental Institute}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastman.ucl.ac.uk/departments/others/library/Eastman-Library-Guide.pdf|title=Eastman Library Guide|accessdate=16 September 2010|publisher=UCL Eastman Dental Institute}}</ref>

All staff and students of the Institute, UCL and the Eastman Dental Hospital are entitled to full membership of the library.<ref name=library/>

